column2:
"Oh, it's been a while!
Hey, what's with that puzzled look?"
"Don't you recognize me? It's me, Enga Yasaka! You helped me out with all that stuff on Earth!"
"Seriously, that's pretty harsh for a joke. I almost thought you really had forgotten me."
"Xiera invited me over. It's been a while since I was last here, but things seem as serious as ever."
"She was talking about White Day, but it seems like kind of a bad time for that. Still, this might be a chance to pay you back."

"You seem pretty busy.
I guess you're in demand."
"I'd expect no less from you. But I'm not going to let you beat me."
"Well, if you have some time to spare, I could use your help with some stuff."
"Just my luck to get caught up in something like this. Some White Day, huh?"

"This White Day stuff....
Hitsugi was going on and on about being grateful...."

"Why me?
I'm no good at stuff like this."
"Sorry, I need to hurry. You'll understand when you're in the same situation. I'm counting on you."

"I came here to repay you for everything you've done...
But in the end, I feel like you just saved me all over again."

"You're saying I did some good?
Heh, I appreciate you saying that."
"Seems like it's all settled for now, so I guess I'll just do my own thing."
"Anyway, it was nice to have fought alongside you again. Thanks for everything."
